Push a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the pasta. Halve, peel
and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2} (or use
a #garlic press{}). Pull a #vegetable peeler{} lengthways along the
@Courgette{1} to make ribbons. Finely chop the @Chives{1}(finely chopped) (use
#scissors{} if you like). Zest and halve the @Lemon{1/2}.

Add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and simmer until cooked,
~{12%minutes}. When ready, reserve some of the pasta cooking water (@Reserved Pasta Water
for the Sauce{100%ml}), then drain the pasta in a #colander{}. Return to the pan and
drizzle over some @oil{} to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a glug of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the
@Rainbow Chard{150%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir-fry until starting
to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the courgette and garlic, mix well and cook for
~{2-3%minutes} more. Once cooked, pop the greens into a #mixing bowl{} and cover with
some foil to keep warm.

Put your frying pan back on medium heat with a splash of @oil{} and add the shallot and
@Chorizo{60%g}. Cook until the shallot is softened and the chorizo starting to brown,
stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}, then add the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and the
reserved pasta water. Stir to combine, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.
Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, heat through until piping hot, then season with
@pepper{}. Stir through most of the grated @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}.

Add the pasta to your sauce along with half the greens and stir everything together.
TIP: If the sauce needs loosening up, just add a splash of water. Add a pinch of
lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt and
pepper if needed.

Serve the creamy pasta in bowls with the remaining greens on top and a sprinkling of
the remaining grated hard Italian style cheese. Enjoy!

> Wilted dark greens combined with a hearty portion of creamy garlicky pasta make this
> recipe a seriously satisfying weeknight supper. If you feel the creamy sauce is a
> little bit thick, add a little bit of the starchy pasta water to loosen up the
> consistency. The salty, starchy water not only adds flavor but helps the sauce cling
> to the rigatoni (this is a great trick that works for all pasta sauces). Buon
> appetito!

> Mod step 4: If you've chosen to add chorizo to your meal, add it to the pan when you
> add the shallot and cook for the same amount of time. Then continue.